moves.1. e4: Another game that I think I played well other than a few mistakes, but I have only been playing for 7 months at this time so mistakes are going to happen. Fell free to comment if you see something I did not. I will try to learn all the abbreviations for pieces and moves in the future but I will do my best for now.
moves.1... e5 2. Nc3 a6 3. Nf3 Bd6 4. Bc4: This is how I was opening up most of the time for awhile. I grew not  so fond of it because if I move my Q pawn to d3 I end up leaving my bishop open for a pawn attack.
moves.4... h6 5. d4: Try to a achieve what I think is the Sicilian defence with a pawn exchange.
moves.5... Nc6 6. a3 Qf6 7. Be3 Nge7: We are both loaded up for a big exchange.
moves.8. d5: Trying to force something to happen. I feel I have control of the center and want to see his reaction to my push.
moves.8... Na7: Don't think that was the best move, but then again I have only been playing for 8 or 9 months. His knight is useless for the time being.
moves.9. Ne2 Ng6 10. Ng3: Preparing for a King side attack.
moves.10... Be7 11. Nf5 d6 12. Nxe7: Maybe I should not have sacrificed, but I definitely feel more comfortable attacking.
moves.12... Qxe7 13. Qe2 Bd7 14. a4: Defending his bishop from advancing to b5. Maybe not a very good move.
moves.14... Qf6 15. h3 O-O 16. g4: After he castles I start to push my pawn attack. I should be able to castle in the next few moves and bring my other rook into the game.
moves.16... Nf4 17. Bxf4: I did not like that knight coming down on me. I struggle sometimes with defending the knight attacks. Maybe I have not been playing long enough to fully understand the best ways to defend them.
I have made him a nice little home for his knight. I am not feeling very comfortable at this point. Even though his knight does not seem to pose a great threat right now.
moves.23... Ng6 24. Rdg1 Qf4 25. h5: Now that my rook's are where I want them I will continue my push with the pawns.
moves.25... Ne7 26. Rh4: Now I feel a little more comfortable attacking his queen.
moves.26... Qg5 27. f4 Qxf4: My atatck is not looking so strong anymore, but I still feel I have the upperhand.
moves.28. Qxf4 exf4 29. Rf1 b5 30. axb5 axb5 3: Now I have him opened up.
moves.36. Rf6 Ra6 37. e5: I will need this pawn to back up my rook. I know he will be moving his King to g7.
moves.38. Rh2 Be6: This was a big mistake. Now I get  a bishop for free.
moves.39. Bxe6 fxe6: Not what I thought he would do. Instead of giving me a bishop for free he gave me his rook in 2 moves.
moves.40. Rg2+ Kh7 41. Rxf8 Nf5 42. Rg6 dxe5 4: His next move was the ending. I guess he overlooked what was coming.
